{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5308.The_Pearl", "title": "The Pearl", "titleComplete": "The Pearl", "description": "Like his father and grandfather before him, Kino is a poor diver, gathering pearls from the gulf beds that once brought great wealth to the kings of Spain and now provide Kino, Juana, and their infant son with meager subsistence. Then, on a day like any other, Kino emerges from the sea with a pearl as large as a sea gull\u2019s egg, as \u201cperfect as the moon.\u201d With the pearl comes hope, the promise of comfort and of security\u2026A story of classic simplicity, based on a Mexican folk tale, The Pearl explores the secrets of man\u2019s nature, greed, the darkest depths of evil, and the luminous possibilities of love.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1437234939i/5308.jpg", "genres": ["Short Stories", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Read For School", "Novella", "Fiction", "Novels", "American", "Literature", "School"], "asin": "0142000698", "isbn": "0142000698", "isbn13": "9780142000694", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "author": ["John Steinbeck"], "publishDate": 1010476800000, "characters": ["Juana", "Juan Tomas", "Kino", "Apolonia", "Coyotito"], "places": ["La Paz", "Loreto, Baja California Sur", "The Gulf", "Santa Rosalia", "Nayarit"], "ratingHistogram": [11488, 24759, 71761, 77525, 45861], "ratingsCount": 231394, "reviewsCount": 12034, "numPages": 96, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32075671-the-hate-u-give", "title": "The Hate U Give", "titleComplete": "The Hate U Give (The Hate U Give, #1)", "description": "An alternate cover edition of ISBN 9780062498533 can be found here.Sixteen-year-old Starr Carter moves between two worlds: the poor neighborhood where she lives and the fancy suburban prep school she attends. The uneasy balance between these worlds is shattered when Starr witnesses the fatal shooting of her childhood best friend Khalil at the hands of a police officer. Khalil was unarmed.Soon afterward, his death is a national headline. Some are calling him a thug, maybe even a drug dealer and a gangbanger. Protesters are taking to the streets in Khalil\u2019s name. Some cops and the local drug lord try to intimidate Starr and her family. What everyone wants to know is: what really went down that night? And the only person alive who can answer that is Starr.But what Starr does\u2014or does not\u2014say could upend her community. It could also endanger her life.Inspired by the Black Lives Matter movement, this is a powerful and gripping YA novel about one girl's struggle for justice.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1476284759i/32075671.jpg", "genres": ["Race", "Realistic Fiction", "Contemporary", "Social Justice", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Coming Of Age", "Young Adult Contemporary", "Teen", "Young Adult"], "asin": "0062498533", "publisher": "Balzer + Bray", "series": ["The Hate U Give"], "author": ["Angie Thomas"], "publishDate": 1488268800000, "characters": ["DeVante (The Hate U Give)", "Kenya (The Hate U Give)", "Chris Bryant", "Lisa Carter", "Carlos Carter", "April Ofrah", "Maverick Carter", "Starr Carter", "Seven Carter", "Maya Yang", "Hailey Grant"], "places": ["Garden Heights, Mississippi", "The United States of America"], "ratingHistogram": [6768, 12738, 65969, 247567, 524313], "ratingsCount": 857355, "reviewsCount": 74366