{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34080.The_Waste_Land", "title": "The Waste Land", "titleComplete": "The Waste Land", "description": "The Waste Land, first published in 1922, is often regarded as T.S. Eliot's masterpiece, as well as one of the most important poems of the 20th century and a central work of modernist poetry.The work, divided in 5 sections, juxtaposes the legend of the Holy Grail and the Fisher King, with a snapshot of early twentieth-century British society. In contemporary times, it is often read published within The Waste Land and Other Poems and has come to be Eliot's most popular poem.\n  T.S. Elliot\n was a poet, essayist, publisher, playwright, literary critic and editor. Born in 1888 in St. Louis (MO, USA), he is considered one of the 20th century's major poets, and a central figure in English-language Modernist poetry.\"In ten years' time,\" wrote Edmund Wilson in Axel's Castle (1931), \"Elliot has left upon English poetry a mark more unmistakable than that of any other poet writing in English.\" In 1948, Eliot was awarded the Nobel Price \"for his work as a trail-blazing pioneer of modern poetry.\"", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1597549396i/34080.jpg", "genres": ["Poetry", "Classics", "British Literature", "Read For School", "College", "Fiction", "American", "Literature", "20th Century", "School"], "asin": "0393974995", "isbn": "0393974995", "isbn13": "9780393974997", "publisher": "W.W. Norton & Company", "author": ["Michael North", "T.S. Eliot"], "publishDate": 978336000000, "ratingHistogram": [1305, 2721, 8733, 16291, 23626], "ratingsCount": 52676, "reviewsCount": 1653, "numPages": 288, "language": "English"}
