{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33124137-pet-sematary", "title": "Pet Sematary", "titleComplete": "Pet Sematary", "description": "'This is an alternate Cover Edition for ASIN: B00K3NEE56. When the Creeds move into a beautiful old house in rural Maine, it all seems too good to be true: physician father, beautiful wife, charming little daughter, adorable infant son-and now an idyllic home. As a family, they've got it all...right down to the friendly car. But the nearby woods hide a blood-chilling truth-more terrifying than death itself-and hideously more powerful. The Creeds are going to learn that sometimes dead is better.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1480069533i/33124137.jpg", "genres": ["Fantasy", "Adult", "Suspense", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Horror", "Paranormal", "Thriller", "Supernatural", "Mystery"], "publisher": "Scribner", "author": ["Stephen King"], "publishDate": 1399964400000, "characters": ["Jud Crandall", "Louis Creed", "Gage Creed", "Victor Pascow", "Rachel Creed", "Ellie Creed"], "places": ["Maine", "Ludlow, Maine"], "ratingHistogram": [7302, 25563, 114664, 203561, 218466], "ratingsCount": 569556, "reviewsCount": 23070, "numPages": 580, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 441792000000, "category": "Best Fantasy Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "World Fantasy Award", "awardedAt": 441792000000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11324204-houdini-heart", "title": "Houdini Heart", "titleComplete": "Houdini Heart", "description": "HOUDINI HEART harkens back to the masters of suspenseful supernatural Poe, Lovecraft, Shirley Jackson, but speaks with a wholly fresh voice. Once caught in its pages, there's no escaping Longfellow's terrible tale. Weeks ago, she was one of Hollywood's biggest writers, wed to one of its greatest stars. The doting mother of their golden child. But now? She's alone, tortured by a horrifying secret no woman could bear. Pursued by those she can't outrun, anguished by a guilt she can't endure, and driven close to madness, she flees to the one place she's ever called a small town in Vermont where River House still stands. To a child, the splendid hotel was mysterious and magical and all its glamorous guests knew delicious secrets.Cocooned in its walls, she will write one last book. Her atonement? Or her suicide note? But life is never as you dream it, and River House isn't what she'd always imagined it was. Intense, literary, and harrowing, Houdini Heart is a tale of bone-chilling horror, emotional torment, and psychological terror. Gripped by River House, trapped in an aging hotel of mirrors only Houdini could escape, how much can haunt a mind before it too is only a thing once imagined? \"A haunting and disturbing journey through the psyche.\"\u2014Erika Mailman, Author of \"The Witch's Trinity\"", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1510418043i/11324204.jpg", "genres": ["Thriller", "Psychological Horror", "Fantasy", "Fiction", "Horror", "Gothic", "Magical Realism", "Literature", "Supernatural", "Mystery"], "asin": "0975925512", "isbn": "0975925512", "isbn13": "9780975925515", "publisher": "Eio Books", "author": ["Ki Longfellow"], "publishDate": 1303714800000, "ratingHistogram": [482, 483, 819, 1698, 2240], "ratingsCount": 5722, "reviewsCount": 228, "numPages": 254, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17716.Waiting_for_Godot", "title": "Waiting for Godot", "titleComplete": "Waiting for Godot", "description": "The story revolves around two seemingly homeless men simply waiting for someone\u2014or something\u2014named Godot. Vladimir and Estragon wait near a tree, inhabiting a drama spun of their own consciousness. The result is a comical wordplay of poetry, dreamscapes, and nonsense, which has been interpreted as mankind\u2019s inexhaustible search for meaning. Beckett\u2019s language pioneered an expressionistic minimalism that captured the existential post-World War II Europe. His play remains one of the most magical and beautiful allegories of our time.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327910301i/17716.jpg", "genres": ["Irish Literature", "Classics", "Theatre", "Fiction", "Philosophy", "Plays", "Literature", "France", "School", "Drama"], "publisher": "Grove", "author": ["Samuel Beckett"], "publishDate": 1293868800000, "characters": ["Estragon", "Pozzo", "boy", "Lucky", "Vladimir (Samuel Beckett)"], "ratingHistogram": [7806, 15956, 42420, 64241, 66299], "ratingsCount": 196722, "reviewsCount": 8364, "numPages": 109, "language": "English"}
