{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/41637836-the-subtle-knife", "title": "The Subtle Knife", "titleComplete": "The Subtle Knife (His Dark Materials, #2)", "description": "She had asked: What is he? A friend or an enemy?The alethiometer answered: He is a murderer.When she saw the answer, she relaxed at once.Lyra finds herself in a shimmering, haunted otherworld \u2013 Citt\u00e0gazze, where soul-eating Spectres stalk the streets and wingbeats of distant angels sound against the sky.But she is not without allies: twelve-year-old Will Parry, fleeing for his life after taking another's, has also stumbled into this strange new realm.On a perilous journey from world to world, Lyra and Will uncover a deadly secret: an object of extraordinary and devastating power.And with every step, they move closer to an even greater threat \u2013 and the shattering truth of their own destiny.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1535965085i/41637836.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Fantasy", "Childrens", "Science Fiction", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Steampunk", "Middle Grade", "Young Adult"], "asin": "B00SSJYF8S", "publisher": "RHCP Digital", "series": ["His Dark Materials"], "author": ["Philip Pullman"], "publishDate": 1535785200000, "characters": ["Serafina Pekkala", "Mary Malone", "Pantalaimon", "Stanislaus Grumman", "Lyra Belacqua", "Marisa Coulter", "Lee Scoresby", "Will Parry", "Hester"], "ratingHistogram": [5420, 15563, 70255, 157432, 180168], "ratingsCount": 428838, "reviewsCount": 12579, "numPages": 370, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Audie Award", "awardedAt": 978336000000, "category": "Children's Titles Ages 8-12", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "North East Teenage Book Award", "awardedAt": 915177600000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12220.A_Streetcar_Named_Desire", "title": "A Streetcar Named Desire", "titleComplete": "A Streetcar Named Desire", "description": "The Pulitzer Prize and Drama Critics Circle Award winning play\u2014reissued with an introduction by Arthur Miller (Death of a Salesman and The Crucible), and Williams\u2019 essay \u201cThe World I Live In.\u201dIt is a very short list of 20th-century American plays that continue to have the same power and impact as when they first appeared\u201457 years after its Broadway premiere, Tennessee Williams\u2019 A Streetcar Named Desire is one of those plays. The story famously recounts how the faded and promiscuous Blanche DuBois is pushed over the edge by her sexy and brutal brother-in-law, Stanley Kowalski. Streetcar launched the careers of Marlon Brando, Jessica Tandy, Kim Hunter, and Karl Malden, and solidified the position of Tennessee Williams as one of the most important young playwrights of his generation, as well as that of Elia Kazan as the greatest American stage director of the \u201940s and \u201950s.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1389153133i/12220.jpg", "genres": ["Classics", "Read For School", "Theatre", "Fiction", "Plays", "American", "Literature", "20th Century", "School", "Drama"], "asin": "0822210894", "isbn": "0822210894", "isbn13": "9780822210894", "publisher": "Dramatists Play Service, Inc.", "author": ["Tennessee Williams"], "publishDate": 883641600000, "characters": ["Blanche DuBois", "Steve Hubbel", "Harold \"Mitch\" Mitchell", "Eunice Hubbel", "Stanley Kowalski", "Stella Kowalski"], "places": ["Louisiana", "New Orleans, Louisiana", "The United States of America"], "ratingHistogram": [5108, 16163, 65503, 111166, 106834], "ratingsCount": 304774, "reviewsCount": 6661, "numPages": 107, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Pulitzer Prize", "awardedAt": -694281600000, "category": "Drama", "hasWon": nu