{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/14905.The_Complete_Novels", "title": "The Complete Novels", "titleComplete": "The Complete Novels", "description": "Few novelists have conveyed the subtleties and nuances of their own social milieu with the wit and insight of Jane Austen. Through her vivacious and spirited heroines and their circle, she paints vivid portraits of English middle-class life as the eighteenth century came to a close. Each of the novels is a love story and a story about marriage \u2014 marriage for love, for financial security, for social status. But they are not mere romances; ironic, comic and wise, they are masterly studies of the society Jane Austen observed. The seven novels in this volume contain some of the most brilliant, dazzling prose in the English language.--back coverEmma / Lady Susan / Mansfield Park / Northanger Abbey / Persuasion / Pride and Prejudice / Sense and Sensibility", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388178574i/14905.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Historical", "Fiction", "Novels", "Classic Literature", "Literature", "British Literature", "Anthologies"], "asin": "0140259449", "isbn": "0140259449", "isbn13": "9780140259445", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "author": ["Jane Austen"], "publishDate": 820483200000, "characters": ["Colonel Brandon", "Maria Bertram", "Mrs. Dashwood", "Eleanor Tilney", "Fanny Dashwood", "Mr. Price", "Isabella Thorpe", "Lady Russell", "Lady Bertram", "Fitzwilliam Darcy", "Mary Bennet", "Kitty Bennet", "Colonel Fitzwilliam", "Mel Horowitz", "Tom Bertram", "Charlotte Lucas", "Lydia Bennet", "Sir William Lucas", "John Dashwood", "Caroline Bingley", "General Tilney", "Mrs. Isabella Knightley", "Mary Crawford", "Augusta Elton", "Mrs. Price", "Julia Bertram", "Edmund Bertram", "Mr. Yates", "Mr. William Collins", "Henry Tilney", "Lady Middleton", "Elinor Dashwood", "Cher", "Charles Bingley", "Catherine Morl