{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3153910-the-art-of-racing-in-the-rain", "title": "The Art of Racing in the Rain", "titleComplete": "The Art of Racing in the Rain", "description": "Enzo knows he is different from other dogs: a philosopher with a nearly human soul (and an obsession with opposable thumbs), he has educated himself by watching television extensively, and by listening very closely to the words of his master, Denny Swift, an up-and-coming race car driver.Through Denny, Enzo has gained tremendous insight into the human condition, and he sees that life, like racing, isn't simply about going fast. On the eve of his death, Enzo takes stock of his life, recalling all that he and his family have been through.A heart-wrenching but deeply funny and ultimately uplifting story of family, love, loyalty, and hope, The Art of Racing in the Rain is a beautifully crafted and captivating look at the wonders and absurdities of human life ... as only a dog could tell it.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1377206302i/3153910.jpg", "genres": ["Contemporary", "Adult", "Adult Fiction", "Audiobook", "Animals", "Fiction", "Dogs", "Family", "Novels", "Book Club"], "asin": "1554681723", "isbn": "1554681723", "isbn13": "9781554681723", "publisher": "Harper Collins", "author": ["Garth Stein"], "publishDate": 1210662000000, "characters": ["Zo\u00eb", "Denny Swift", "Enzo", "Eve"], "places": ["Washington (state)", "Seattle, Washington", "Pacific Northwest"], "ratingHistogram": [6458, 18326, 73474, 169074, 244480], "ratingsCount": 511812, "reviewsCount": 43331, "numPages": 336, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12000020-aristotle-and-dante-discover-the-secrets-of-the-universe", "title": "Aristotle and Dante Discover the Secrets of the Universe", "titleComplete": "Aristotle and Dante Discover the Secrets of the Universe (Aristotle and Dante, #1)", "description": "Dante can swim. Ari can't. Dante is articulate and self-assured. Ari has a hard time with words and suffers from self-doubt. Dante gets lost in poetry and art. Ari gets lost in thoughts of his older brother who is in prison. Dante is fair skinned. Ari's features are much darker. It seems that a boy like Dante, with his open and unique perspective on life, would be the last person to break down the walls that Ari has built around himself.But against all odds, when Ari and Dante meet, they develop a special bond that will teach them the most important truths of their lives, and help define the people they want to be. But there are big hurdles in their way, and only by believing in each other\u2015and the power of their friendship\u2015can Ari and Dante emerge stronger on the other side.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1328320260i/12000020.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Realistic Fiction", "LGBT", "Contemporary", "Gay", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Coming Of Age", "Queer", "Young Adult"], "asin": "1442408928", "isbn": "1442408928", "isbn13": "9781442408920", "publisher": "Simon & Schuster Books for Young Readers", "series": ["Aristotle and Dante"], "author": ["Benjamin Alire S\u00e1enz"], "publishDate": 1329811200000, "characters": ["Aristotle \"Ari\" Mendoza", "Dante Quintana"], "places": ["Texas", "El Paso, Texas"], "ratingHistogram": [8231, 16944, 67361, 169823, 310648], "ratingsCount": 573007, "reviewsCount": 70240, "numPages": 390, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Stonewall Book Award", "awardedAt": 1357027200000, "category": "Children\u2019s and Young Adult Literature", "hasWon": null}, {"name":