{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/44186.The_Monster_at_the_End_of_this_Book", "title": "The Monster at the End of this Book", "titleComplete": "The Monster at the End of this Book", "description": "\n  \"On the first page, what did that say? Did that say there will be a Monster at the end of the book???\"\nRead along as Grover begs you not to turn the page\u2014because there is a monster at this end of this book!Lovable, furry old Grover is distressed to learn that there's a monster at the end of this book! He begs readers not to turn the pages, but of course kids feel they just have to see this monster for themselves. Grover is astonished\u2014and toddlers will be delighted\u2014to discover who is really the monster at the end of the book!Many adults name this book as their favorite Little Golden Book. This all-time favorite is now available as a Big Little Golden Book\u2014perfect for lap-time reading.\n  Jon Stone\n (1931\u20131997) is the author of this book, but he was also Sesame Street's principal director until 1996. Working with Jim Henson, he helped create many of the Muppet characters, including Big Bird and Cookie Monster. He was also responsible for the show's format and setting. Stone contributed occasional announcer voices (such as the soap opera promo spoof \"School in the Afternoon\"), and served similar duty on two Muppet Meeting Films. Stone died of complications from Lou Gehrig's disease on March 30th, 1997. In his New York Times obituary, Joan Ganz Cooney describes Stone as \"probably the most brilliant writer of children's television material in America\".", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388193494i/44186.jpg", "genres": ["Classics", "Humor", "Fantasy", "Childrens", "Kids", "Fiction", "Picture Books", "Storytime", "Juvenile", "Monsters"], "asin": "037582913X", "isbn": "037582913X", "isbn13": "9780375829130", "publisher": "Golden Books", "series": ["Big Little Golden