{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10959.Sophie_s_World", "title": "Sophie's World", "titleComplete": "Sophie's World", "description": "An alternative cover for this ISBN can be found hereOne day fourteen-year-old Sophie Amundsen comes home from school to find in her mailbox two notes, with one question on each: \"Who are you?\" and \"Where does the world come from?\" From that irresistible beginning, Sophie becomes obsessed with questions that take her far beyond what she knows of her Norwegian village. Through those letters, she enrolls in a kind of correspondence course, covering Socrates to Sartre, with a mysterious philosopher, while receiving letters addressed to another girl. Who is Hilde? And why does her mail keep turning up? To unravel this riddle, Sophie must use the philosophy she is learning\u2014but the truth turns out to be far more complicated than she could have imagined.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1343459906i/10959.jpg", "genres": ["Classics", "Contemporary", "Fantasy", "Unfinished", "Fiction", "Scandinavian Literature", "Philosophy", "Novels", "Literature", "Young Adult"], "asin": "1857993284", "isbn": "1857993284", "isbn13": "9781857993288", "publisher": "Phoenix", "author": ["Jostein Gaarder", "Paulette M\u00f8ller"], "publishDate": 788947200000, "characters": ["Malaikat Ariel", "Sigmund Freud", "Sofie Amundsen", "Charles Darwin", "Ren\u00e9 Descartes", "David Hume", "George Berkeley", "St. Augustine", "Jorunn", "Jesus", "Thomas Aquinas", "Socrates (philosopher)", "John Locke", "Karl Marx", "Aristotle (philosopher)", "Plato", "Immanuel Kant", "Baruch Spinoza", "Cecilia Skotbu"], "places": ["Norway"], "ratingHistogram": [6122, 15296, 52057, 89516, 91074], "ratingsCount": 254065, "reviewsCount": 14608, "numPages": 403, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Buxtehuder Bulle", "awardedAt": 820483200000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Premio Bancar