{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4687.The_Cider_House_Rules", "title": "The Cider House Rules", "titleComplete": "The Cider House Rules", "description": "Raised from birth in the orphanage at St. Cloud's, Maine, Homer Wells has become the protege of Dr. Wilbur Larch, its physician and director. There Dr. Larch cares for the troubled mothers who seek his help, either by delivering and taking in their unwanted babies or by performing illegal abortions. Meticulously trained by Dr. Larch, Homer assists in the former, but draws the line at the latter. Then a young man brings his beautiful fiancee to Dr. Larch for an abortion, and everything about the couple beckons Homer to the wide world outside the orphanage ...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327962519i/4687.jpg", "genres": ["Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Contemporary", "Historical", "Adult Fiction", "Fiction", "Novels", "American", "Literature", "Literary Fiction"], "asin": "0786226749", "isbn": "0786226749", "isbn13": "9780786226740", "publisher": "Thorndike Press", "author": ["John Irving"], "publishDate": 946713600000, "characters": ["Wally Worthington", "Candy Kendall", "Dr. Wilbur Larch", "Rose Rose", "Homer Wells"], "places": ["Maine", "St. Cloud's, Maine", "Three Mile Falls, Maine"], "ratingHistogram": [1625, 5332, 29196, 72797, 73487], "ratingsCount": 182437, "reviewsCount": 4954, "numPages": 1064, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3236307-graceling", "title": "Graceling", "titleComplete": "Graceling (Graceling Realm, #1)", "description": "Katsa has been able to kill a man with her bare hands since she was eight\u2014she\u2019s a Graceling, one of the rare people in her land born with an extreme skill. As niece of the king, she should be able to live a life of privilege, but Graced as she is with killing, she is forced to work as the king\u2019s thug. She never expects to fall in love with beautiful Prince Po. She never expects to learn the truth behind her Grace\u2014or the terrible secret that lies hidden far away . . . a secret that could destroy all seven kingdoms with words alone. With elegant, evocative prose and a cast of unforgettable characters, debut author Kristin Cashore creates a mesmerizing world, a death-defying adventure, and a heart-racing romance that will consume you, hold you captive, and leave you wanting more.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1331548394i/3236307.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "High Fantasy", "Adventure", "Fantasy", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Magic", "Young Adult Fantasy", "Teen", "Young Adult"], "asin": "015206396X", "isbn13": "9780152063962", "publisher": "Harcourt", "series": ["Graceling Realm"], "author": ["Kristin Cashore"], "publishDate": 1222844400000, "characters": ["Po (Graceling Realm)", "Randa (Graceling Realm)", "Katsa (Graceling Realm)", "Leck (Graceling Realm)", "Bitterblue", "Grandfather Tealiff"], "ratingHistogram": [11512, 22729, 77626, 152888, 188903], "ratingsCount": 453658, "reviewsCount": 26437, "numPages": 471, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 1230796800000, "category": "Best First Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Mythopoeic Fantasy Award", "awardedAt": 1230796800000, "category": "Children's Literature", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "William C. Morris YA Debut Award", "awardedAt": 1230796800