{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6339664-hush-hush", "title": "Hush, Hush", "titleComplete": "Hush, Hush (Hush, Hush, #1)", "description": "A SACRED OATHA FALLEN ANGELA FORBIDDEN LOVERomance was not part of Nora Grey's plan. She's never been particularly attracted to the boys at her school, no matter how hard her best friend, Vee, pushes them at her. Not until Patch comes along. With his easy smile and eyes that seem to see inside her, Patch draws Nora to him against her better judgment.But after a series of terrifying encounters, Nora's not sure whom to trust. Patch seems to be everywhere she is and seems to know more about her than her closest friends. She can't decide whether she should fall into his arms or run and hide. And when she tries to seek some answers, she finds herself near a truth that is way more unsettling than anything Patch makes her feel.For she is right in the middle of an ancient battle between the immortal and those that have fallen - and, when it comes to choosing sides, the wrong choice will cost Nora her life.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1358261334i/6339664.jpg", "genres": ["Angels", "Romance", "Fantasy", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Paranormal Romance", "Young Adult Fantasy", "Supernatural", "Urban Fantasy", "Young Adult"], "asin": "1416989412", "isbn": "1416989412", "isbn13": "9781416989417", "publisher": "Simon & Schuster", "series": ["Hush, Hush"], "author": ["Becca Fitzpatrick"], "publishDate": 1255417200000, "characters": ["Rixon", "Vee Sky", "Nora Grey", "Marcie Millar", "Elliot Saunders", "Jev \"Patch\" Cipriano"], "places": ["Coldwater, Maine"], "ratingHistogram": [30959, 55810, 133842, 181503, 288980], "ratingsCount": 691094, "reviewsCount": 29308, "numPages": 391, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Goodreads Choice Award", "awardedAt": 1230796800000, "category": "Young Adult Series", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/472331.Watchmen", "title": "Watchmen", "titleComplete": "Watchmen", "description": "This Hugo Award-winning graphic novel chronicles the fall from grace of a group of super-heroes plagued by all-too-human failings. Along the way, the concept of the super-hero is dissected as the heroes are stalked by an unknown assassin.One of the most influential graphic novels of all time and a perennial best-seller, Watchmen has been studied on college campuses across the nation and is considered a gateway title, leading readers to other graphic novels such as V for Vendetta, Batman: The Dark Knight Returns and The Sandman series.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1442239711i/472331.jpg", "genres": ["Classics", "Dc Comics", "Superheroes", "Dystopia", "Graphic Novels Comics", "Adult", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Science Fiction", "Comics Manga", "Mystery"], "asin": "0930289234", "isbn": "0930289234", "isbn13": "9780930289232", "publisher": "DC Comics", "series": ["Watchmen", "I Classici del Fumetto di Repubblica - Serie Oro"], "author": ["Alan Moore", "John    Higgins", "Dave Gibbons"], "publishDate": 1104566400000, "characters": ["Hollis Mason", "Rorschach", "Sally Jupiter", "Daniel Dreiberg", "Adrian Veidt", "Edward Blake", "Dr. Manhattan", "Laurel Jupiter"], "places": ["New York City, New York"], "ratingHistogram": [8373, 14860, 56476, 151395, 317885], "ratingsCount": 548989, "reviewsCount": 16999, "numPages": 416, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Hugo Award", "awardedAt": 568022400000, "category": "Other Forms", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 568022400000, "category": "Best Non-Fiction/Art", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Harvey Awards", "awardedAt": 568022400000, "category": "Best Writer (for Alan Moore), Best Artist or Penciller (for Dave Gibbons), Best Continuing or Limited Series, Best Single Issue (\"Watchmen #9\"), Best Graphic Alb