{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3431.The_Five_People_You_Meet_in_Heaven", "title": "The Five People You Meet in Heaven", "titleComplete": "The Five People You Meet in Heaven", "description": "From the author of the phenomenal #1 New York Times bestseller Tuesdays with Morrie, a novel that explores the unexpected connections of our lives, and the idea that heaven is more than a place; it's an answer. Eddie is a wounded war veteran, an old man who has lived, in his mind, an uninspired life. His job is fixing rides at a seaside amusement park. On his 83rd birthday, a tragic accident kills him as he tries to save a little girl from a falling cart. He awakes in the afterlife, where he learns that heaven is not a destination. It's a place where your life is explained to you by five people, some of whom you knew, others who may have been strangers. One by one, from childhood to soldier to old age, Eddie's five people revisit their connections to him on earth, illuminating the mysteries of his \"meaningless\" life, and revealing the haunting secret behind the eternal question: \"Why was I here?\"", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388200541i/3431.jpg", "genres": ["Classics", "Inspirational", "Contemporary", "Fantasy", "Adult", "Adult Fiction", "Fiction", "Spirituality", "Philosophy", "Novels"], "asin": "1401308589", "publisher": "Hyperion", "series": ["The Five People You Meet in Heaven"], "author": ["Mitch Albom"], "publishDate": 1064300400000, "characters": ["Blue Man", "Ruby", "Tala", "Eddie", "Marguerite", "Steve Rogers"], "places": ["The United States of America"], "ratingHistogram": [15868, 42568, 146131, 230878, 266369], "ratingsCount": 701814, "reviewsCount": 27334, "numPages": 196, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Lincoln Award", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/233093.The_Cat_in_the_Hat", "title": "The Cat in the Hat", "titleComplete": "The Cat in the Hat (The Cat in the Hat, #1)", "description": "Have a ball with Dr. Seuss and the Cat in the Hat in this classic picture book...but don't forget to clean up your mess! Then he said That is that.And then he was goneWith a tip of his hat.A dreary day turns into a wild romp when this beloved story introduces readers to the Cat in the Hat and his troublemaking friends, Thing 1 and Thing 2 \u2013 And don't forget Fish! A favorite among kids, parents and teachers, this story uses simple words and basic rhyme to encourage and delight beginning readers.Originally created by \n  Dr. Seuss\n himself, Beginner Books are fun, funny, and easy to read. These unjacketed hardcover early readers encourage children to read all on their own, using simple words and illustrations. Smaller than the classic large format Seuss picture books like The Lorax and Oh, The Places You'll Go!, these portable packages are perfect for practicing readers ages 3-7, and lucky parents too!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1468890477i/233093.jpg", "genres": ["Poetry", "Classics", "Humor", "Fantasy", "Childrens", "Kids", "Animals", "Fiction", "Cats", "Picture Books"], "asin": "039480001X", "isbn": "039480001X", "isbn13": "9780394800011", "publisher": "Random House Books for Young Readers", "series": ["The Cat in the Hat"], "author": ["Dr. Seuss"], "publishDate": 473414400000, "characters": ["The Cat in the Hat"], "ratingHistogram": [13428, 24170, 86233, 131354, 272031], "ratingsCount": 527216, "reviewsCount": 7027, "numPages": 61, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Books I Loved Best Yearly (BILBY) Awards", "awardedAt": 1072944000000, "category": "Early Readers (2004, 2012)", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30165203-american-gods", "title": "American Gods", "titleComplete": "American Gods", "description": "Days before his release from prison, Shadow's wife, Laura, dies in a mysterious car crash. Numbly, he makes his way back home. On the plane, he encounters the enigmatic Mr Wednesday, who claims to be a refugee from a distant war, a former god and the king of America. Together they embark on a profoundly strange journey across the heart of the USA, whilst all around them a storm of preternatural and epic proportions threatens to break.Scary, gripping and deeply unsettling, American Gods takes a long, hard look into the soul of America. You'll be surprised by what - and who - it finds there...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1462924585i/30165203.jpg", "genres": ["Contemporary", "Fantasy", "Science Fiction", "Adult", "Mythology", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Horror", "Urban Fantasy"], "publisher": "William Morrow", "series": ["American Gods"], "author": ["Neil Gaiman"], "publishDate": 1308639600000, "characters": ["Easter", "Mr. Ibis", "Mr. Town", "Samantha Black Crow", "Mad Sweeney", "Spider", "Mr. Wednesday", "Laura Moon", "Technical Boy", "Hinzelmann", "Chad Mulligan", "Czernobog", "Bilquis", "Mr. Jacquel", "Mr. Nancy", "Odin (Norse mythology)", "Loki", "Margaret Black Crow", "Shadow Moon", "Media", "Mr. World", "Whiskey Jack"], "places": ["Wisconsin", "Chattanooga, Tennessee", "Minnesota", "Chicago, Illinois", "The United States of America", "Illinois"], "ratingHistogram": [18250, 44542, 147388, 310978, 388770], "ratingsCount": 909928, "reviewsCount": 46135, "numPages": 635, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Bram Stoker Award", "awardedAt": 978336000000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Hugo Award", "awardedAt": 1009872000000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Nebula Award", "awarded