{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30183.Marked", "title": "Marked", "titleComplete": "Marked (House of Night, #1)", "description": "Also see: Alternate Cover Editions for this ISBN [ACE]  \n  ACE #1\nAfter a Vampire Tracker Marks her with a crescent moon on her forehead, 16-year-old Zoey Redbird enters the House of Night and learns that she is no average fledgling. She has been Marked as special by the vampyre Goddess Nyx and has affinities for all five elements: Air, Fire, Water, Earth and Spirit. But she is not the only fledgling at the House of Night with special powers. When she discovers that the leader of the Dark Daughters, the school\u2019s most elite club, is misusing her Goddess-given gifts, Zoey must look deep within herself for the courage to embrace her destiny\u2014with a little help from her new vampyre friends (or Nerd Herd, as Aphrodite calls them).", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1317067002i/30183.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Fantasy", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Paranormal Romance", "Magic", "Supernatural", "Vampires", "Urban Fantasy", "Young Adult"], "asin": "0312360266", "isbn": "0312360266", "isbn13": "9780312360269", "publisher": "St. Martin's Press", "series": ["House of Night"], "author": ["P.C. Cast", "Kristin Cast"], "publishDate": 1178002800000, "characters": ["Neferet", "Erik Night", "Heath Luck", "Erin Bates", "Sylvia Redbird", "Nyx (House of Night)", "Damien Maslin", "Shaunee Cole", "Zoey Redbird", "Aphrodite LaFont", "Stevie Rae Johnson"], "places": ["Tulsa, Oklahoma", "Oklahoma", "The United States of America"], "ratingHistogram": [27324, 43834, 105684, 127664, 181694], "ratingsCount": 486200, "reviewsCount": 16030, "numPages": 306, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Romantic Times Reviewers' Choice Award (RT Award)", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": "Young Adult", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33.The_Lord_of_the_Rings", "title": "The Lord of the Rings", "titleComplete": "The Lord of the Rings", "description": "One Ring to rule them all, One Ring to find them, One Ring to bring them all and in the darkness bind themIn ancient times the Rings of Power were crafted by the Elven-smiths, and Sauron, the Dark Lord, forged the One Ring, filling it with his own power so that he could rule all others. But the One Ring was taken from him, and though he sought it throughout Middle-earth, it remained lost to him. After many ages it fell by chance into the hands of the hobbit Bilbo Baggins.From Sauron's fastness in the Dark Tower of Mordor, his power spread far and wide. Sauron gathered all the Great Rings to him, but always he searched for the One Ring that would complete his dominion.When Bilbo reached his eleventy-first birthday he disappeared, bequeathing to his young cousin Frodo the Ruling Ring and a perilous quest: to journey across Middle-earth, deep into the shadow of the Dark Lord, and destroy the Ring by casting it into the Cracks of Doom.The Lord of the Rings tells of the great quest undertaken by Frodo and the Fellowship of the Ring: Gandalf the Wizard; the hobbits Merry, Pippin, and Sam; Gimli the Dwarf; Legolas the Elf; Boromir of Gondor; and a tall, mysterious stranger called Strider.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1566425108i/33.jpg", "genres": ["High Fantasy", "Classics", "Adventure", "Fantasy", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Epic Fantasy", "Fiction", "Novels", "Literature", "Young Adult"], "publisher": "Houghton Mifflin Harcourt", "series": ["The Lord of the Rings"], "author": ["J.R.R. Tolkien"], "publishDate": 1129100400000, "characters": ["Bilbo Baggins", "Legolas", "Peregrin Took", "Saruman", "\u00c9omer", "Gimli", "Sam Gamgee", "Boromir", "Faramir", "Elrond Half-elven", "Gollum", "Aragorn", "\u00c9owyn", "Arwen Und\u00f3miel", "Galadri