{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10975.The_Sound_and_the_Fury", "title": "The Sound and the Fury", "titleComplete": "The Sound and the Fury", "description": "The tragedy of the Compson family features some of the most memorable characters in literature: beautiful, rebellious Caddy; the manchild Benjy; haunted, neurotic Quentin; Jason, the brutal cynic; and Dilsey, their black servant. Their lives fragmented and harrowed by history and legacy, the character\u2019s voices and actions mesh to create what is arguably Faulkner\u2019s masterpiece and one of the greatest novels of the twentieth century.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1433089995i/10975.jpg", "genres": ["Classics", "Southern", "Fiction", "Novels", "American", "Literature", "20th Century", "School", "Southern Gothic", "Literary Fiction"], "publisher": "Vintage International", "author": ["William Faulkner"], "publishDate": 654764400000, "characters": ["Dilsey Gibson", "Caroline Bascomb Compson", "Jason Compson III", "Miss Quentin Compson", "Luster", "Jason Compson IV", "Candace \"Caddy\" Compson", "Benjamin \"Benjy\" Compson", "Quentin Compson III"], "places": ["Mississippi", "Jefferson, Mississippi", "Yoknapatawpha County, Mississippi", "The United States of America"], "ratingHistogram": [8776, 14744, 35367, 54961, 65266], "ratingsCount": 179114, "reviewsCount": 9045, "numPages": 366, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/9328.The_House_of_the_Spirits", "title": "The House of the Spirits", "titleComplete": "The House of the Spirits", "description": "In one of the most important and beloved Latin American works of the twentieth century, Isabel Allende weaves a luminous tapestry of three generations of the Trueba family, revealing both triumphs and tragedies. Here is patriarch Esteban, whose wild desires and political machinations are tempered only by his love for his ethereal wife, Clara, a woman touched by an otherworldly hand. Their daughter, Blanca, whose forbidden love for a man Esteban has deemed unworthy infuriates her father, yet will produce his greatest joy: his granddaughter Alba, a beautiful, ambitious girl who will lead the family and their country into a revolutionary future.The House of the Spirits is an enthralling saga that spans decades and lives, twining the personal and the political into an epic novel of love, magic, and fate.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1621672028i/9328.jpg", "genres": ["Historical Fiction", "Fantasy", "Historical", "Literature", "Fiction", "Novels", "Magical Realism", "Latin American", "Spanish Literature", "Literary Fiction"], "asin": "0553383809", "isbn": "0553383809", "isbn13": "9780553383805", "publisher": "Dial Press Trade Paperback", "series": ["Involuntary trilogy"], "author": ["Magda Bogin", "Isabel Allende"], "publishDate": 1125385200000, "characters": ["Alba Trueba", "Jaime Trueba", "Clara del Valle", "Esteban Garcia", "Nicol\u00e0s Trueba", "Pedro Tercero Garcia", "F\u00e9rula Trueba", "Blanca Trueba", "Esteban Trueba"], "places": ["Chile"], "ratingHistogram": [2380, 7383, 34070, 87748, 126825], "ratingsCount": 258406, "reviewsCount": 14133, "numPages": 448, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Deutscher H\u00f6rbuchpreis", "awardedAt": 1293868800000, "category": "Beste Fiktion", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Prix d