{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/40495148-blindness", "title": "Blindness", "titleComplete": "Blindness", "description": "From Nobel Prize\u2013winning author Jos\u00e9 Saramago, a magnificent, mesmerizing parable of lossA city is hit by an epidemic of \"white blindness\" that spares no one. Authorities confine the blind to an empty mental hospital, but there the criminal element holds everyone captive, stealing food rations, and assaulting women. There is one eyewitness to this nightmare who guides her charges\u2014among them a boy with no mother, a girl with dark glasses, a dog of tears\u2014through the barren streets, and their procession becomes as uncanny as the surroundings are harrowing. As Blindness reclaims the age-old story of a plague, it evokes the vivid and trembling horrors of the twentieth century, leaving readers with a powerful vision of the human spirit that's bound both by weakness and exhilarating strength.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1528481068i/40495148.jpg", "genres": ["Nobel Prize", "Classics", "Dystopia", "Science Fiction", "Portuguese Literature", "Fiction", "Horror", "Novels", "Literature", "Portugal"], "asin": "B003T0GBOM", "publisher": "Mariner Books", "series": ["Blindness"], "author": ["Giovanni Pontiero", "Jos\u00e9 Saramago"], "publishDate": 1377241200000, "characters": ["The first blind man's wife", "The girl with the dark glasses", "The first blind man", "The doctor (Blindness)", "The car thief", "The boy with the squint", "The doctor's wife", "The old man with the black eye patch"], "places": ["Portugal"], "ratingHistogram": [4855, 11715, 40278, 98088, 124641], "ratingsCount": 279577, "reviewsCount": 23130, "numPages": 349, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Premio San Clemente", "awardedAt": 915177600000, "category": "Lingua estranxeira", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Dublin Literary Award", "awardedAt": 915177600000, "category": "", "hasWo