{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/561909.The_Hiding_Place", "title": "The Hiding Place: The Triumphant True Story of Corrie Ten Boom", "titleComplete": "The Hiding Place: The Triumphant True Story of Corrie Ten Boom", "description": "At one time Corrie ten Boom would have laughed at the idea that there would ever be a story to tell. For the first fifty years of her life nothing at all out of the ordinary had ever happened to her. She was an old-maid watchmaker living contentedly with her spinster sister and their elderly father in the tiny Dutch house over their shop. Their uneventful days, as regulated as their own watches, revolved around their abiding love for one another. However, with the Nazi invasion and occupation of Holland, a story did ensue. Corrie ten Boom and her family became leaders in the Dutch Underground, hiding Jewish people in their home in a specially built room and aiding their escape from the Nazis. For their help, all but Corrie found death in a concentration camp. The Hiding Place is their story.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1320418824i/561909.jpg", "genres": ["Christian", "Holocaust", "Biography", "Classics", "Memoir", "Historical", "World War II", "Biography Memoir", "History", "Nonfiction"], "asin": "0553256696", "isbn": "0553256696", "isbn13": "9780553256697", "publisher": "Bantam", "author": ["Elizabeth Sherrill", "John Sherrill", "Corrie ten Boom"], "publishDate": 149842800000, "places": ["Haarlem", "Ravensbr\u00fcck", "Netherlands"], "ratingHistogram": [6152, 7367, 27291, 70899, 203941], "ratingsCount": 315650, "reviewsCount": 13205, "numPages": 242, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30118.A_Light_in_the_Attic", "title": "A Light in the Attic", "titleComplete": "A Light in the Attic", "description": "Last night while I lay thinking here Some Whatifs crawled inside my ear And pranced and partied all night long And sang their same old Whatif song: Whatif I flunk that test?Whatif green hair grows on my chest?Whatif nobody likes me?Whatif a bolt of lightning strikes me?...This 20th anniversary of Shel Silverstein's A Light in the Attic includes a CD of highlights from his Grammy Award-winning album.Here in the attic of Shel Silverstein you will find Backward Bill, Sour Face Ann, the Meehoo with an Exactlywatt, and the Polar Bear in the Frigidaire. You will talk with Broiled Face, and find out what happens when Somebody steals your knees, you get caught by the Quick-Digesting Gink, a Mountain snores, and They Put a Brassiere on the Camel.From the creator of the beloved poetry collections Where the Sidewalk Ends and Falling Up, here is another wondrous book of poems and drawings.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1427169918i/30118.jpg", "genres": ["Banned Books", "Poetry", "Classics", "Humor", "Childrens", "Fiction", "Picture Books", "Juvenile", "Middle Grade", "Young Adult"], "asin": "0060513063", "isbn": "0060513063", "isbn13": "9780060513061", "publisher": "Harpercollins Childrens Books", "author": ["Shel Silverstein"], "publishDate": 1033974000000, "ratingHistogram": [7077, 11954, 52362, 113754, 250913], "ratingsCount": 436060, "reviewsCount": 3372, "numPages": 176, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "George C. Stone Center for Children's Books Recognition of Merit Award", "awardedAt": 441792000000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Magnesia Litera", "awardedAt": 1420099200000, "category": "Translation (Litera za p\u0159ekladovou knihu)", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Garden State Book Award", "awardedAt": null, "category":