{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13623848-the-song-of-achilles", "title": "The Song of Achilles", "titleComplete": "The Song of Achilles", "description": "Alternate cover edition of ISBN 9780062060624.Achilles, \"the best of all the Greeks,\" son of the cruel sea goddess Thetis and the legendary king Peleus, is strong, swift, and beautiful, irresistible to all who meet him. Patroclus is an awkward young prince, exiled from his homeland after an act of shocking violence. Brought together by chance, they forge an inseparable bond, despite risking the gods' wrath.They are trained by the centaur Chiron in the arts of war and medicine, but when word comes that Helen of Sparta has been kidnapped, all the heroes of Greece are called upon to lay siege to Troy in her name. Seduced by the promise of a glorious destiny, Achilles joins their cause, and torn between love and fear for his friend, Patroclus follows. Little do they know that the cruel Fates will test them both as never before and demand a terrible sacrifice.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1357177533i/13623848.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Historical Fiction", "LGBT", "Fantasy", "Historical", "Retellings", "Mythology", "Fiction", "Greek Mythology", "Queer"], "publisher": "Ecco", "author": ["Madeline Miller"], "publishDate": 1346137200000, "characters": ["Achilles", "Odysseus", "Hector of Troy", "Briseis", "Peleus", "Thetis", "Chiron", "Patroclus", "Agamemnon"], "places": ["Troy", "Greece", "Ancient Greece"], "ratingHistogram": [16465, 41780, 156248, 395418, 746738], "ratingsCount": 1356649, "reviewsCount": 147265, "numPages": 408, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Stonewall Book Award", "awardedAt": 1357027200000, "category": "Literature", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Orange Prize", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Gaylactic Spectrum Award", "awardedAt": 1357027200000, "category": "Be