{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5060378-the-girl-who-played-with-fire", "title": "The Girl Who Played with Fire", "titleComplete": "The Girl Who Played with Fire (Millennium, #2)", "description": "The ExposeMillenium publisher Mikael Blomkvist has made his reputation exposing corrupt establishment figures. So when a young journalist approaches him with an investigation into sex trafficking, Blomkvist cannot resist waging war on the powerful figures who control this lucrative industry.The MurderWhen a young couple is found dead in their Stockholm apartment, it's a straightforward job for Inspector Bublanski and his team. The killer left the weapon at the scene - and the fingerprints on the gun point in only one direction.The Girl Who Played with FireEx-security analyst Lisbeth Salander is wanted for murder. Her history of unpredictable and vengeful behaviour makes her an official danger to society - but no-one can find her. The only way Salander can be reached is by computer. But she can break into almost any network she chooses...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1351778881i/5060378.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery Thriller", "Sweden", "Crime", "Contemporary", "Adult", "Suspense", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Thriller", "Mystery"], "asin": "0307269981", "isbn": "0307269981", "isbn13": "9780307269980", "publisher": "Alfred A. Knopf", "series": ["Millennium", "Millennium Split-Volume Edition"], "author": ["Stieg Larsson", "Reg Keeland"], "publishDate": 1248764400000, "characters": ["Carl-Magnus Lundin", "Sonja Modig", "Peter Teleborian", "Holger Palmgren", "Nils Bjurman", "Miriam Wu", "Mikael Blomkvist", "Alexander Zalachenko", "Dragan Armansky", "Erika Berger", "Gunnar Bj\u00f6rck", "Harriet Vanger", "Jan Bublanski", "Lisbeth Salander", "Ronald Niedermann", "Annika Giannini"], "places": ["Stockholm", "Sweden"], "ratingHistogram": [7192, 20909, 119542, 351143, 410688], "ratingsCount": 909474, "revie