{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3836.Don_Quixote", "title": "Don Quixote", "titleComplete": "Don Quixote", "description": "Don Quixote has become so entranced by reading chivalric romances that he determines to become a knight-errant himself. In the company of his faithful squire, Sancho Panza, his exploits blossom in all sorts of wonderful ways. While Quixote's fancy often leads him astray\u2014he tilts at windmills, imagining them to be giants\u2014Sancho acquires cunning and a certain sagacity. Sane madman and wise fool, they roam the world together, and together they have haunted readers' imaginations for nearly four hundred years.With its experimental form and literary playfulness, Don Quixote has been generally recognized as the first modern novel. The book has been enormously influential on a host of writers, from Fielding and Sterne to Flaubert, Dickens, Melville, and Faulkner, who reread it once a year, \"just as some people read the Bible.\"", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1546112331i/3836.jpg", "genres": ["Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Adventure", "Humor", "Fiction", "Spain", "Novels", "Classic Literature", "Spanish Literature", "Literature"], "asin": "0142437239", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "author": ["Miguel de Cervantes Saavedra", "Roberto Gonz\u00e1lez Echevarr\u00eda", "John Rutherford"], "publishDate": 1046160000000, "characters": ["Don Quijote de la Mancha", "Sancho Panza"], "places": ["Spain", "La Mancha", "Barcelona, Catalonia"], "ratingHistogram": [7447, 19262, 60151, 83594, 93206], "ratingsCount": 263660, "reviewsCount": 11697, "numPages": 1023, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Will Eisner Comic Industry Awards", "awardedAt": 1388563200000, "category": "Best Adaptation from Another Medium & Best Humor Publication", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "\u0392\u03c1\u03b1\u03b2\u03b5\u03af\u03bf \u039b\u03bf\u03b3\u03bf\u03c4\u03b5\u03c7\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u0