{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/43641.Water_for_Elephants", "title": "Water for Elephants", "titleComplete": "Water for Elephants", "description": "When Jacob Jankowski, recently orphaned and suddenly adrift, jumps onto a passing train, he enters a world of freaks, drifters, and misfits, a second-rate circus struggling to survive during the Great Depression, making one-night stands in town after endless town. A veterinary student who almost earned his degree, Jacob is put in charge of caring for the circus menagerie. It is there that he meets Marlena, the beautiful young star of the equestrian act, who is married to August, the charismatic but twisted animal trainer. He also meets Rosie, an elephant who seems untrainable until he discovers a way to reach her. Beautifully written, Water for Elephants is illuminated by a wonderful sense of time and place. It tells a story of a love between two people that overcomes incredible odds in a world in which even love is a luxury that few can afford.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1667708346i/43641.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Historical Fiction", "Contemporary", "Historical", "Adult", "Adult Fiction", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Novels", "Book Club"], "asin": "1565125606", "isbn": "1565125606", "isbn13": "9781565125605", "publisher": "Algonquin Books", "author": ["Sara Gruen"], "publishDate": 1176102000000, "characters": ["Rosemary (Water for Elephants)", "Rosie Noah", "August (Water for Elephants)", "Marlena L'Arche", "Jacob Jankowski", "Kinko/Walter", "Camel", "Uncle Al"], "places": ["Joliet, Illinois", "Ithaca, New York", "The United States of America"], "ratingHistogram": [22588, 65470, 273178, 585538, 639160], "ratingsCount": 1585934, "reviewsCount": 61974, "numPages": 368, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Book Sense Book of the Year Award", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": "Adult Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "ALA Al