{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7604.Lolita", "title": "Lolita", "titleComplete": "Lolita", "description": "Librarian's note: Alternate cover edition of ISBN 9780141182537.Humbert Humbert - scholar, aesthete and romantic - has fallen completely and utterly in love with Dolores Haze, his landlady's gum-snapping, silky skinned twelve-year-old daughter. Reluctantly agreeing to marry Mrs Haze just to be close to Lolita, Humbert suffers greatly in the pursuit of romance; but when Lo herself starts looking for attention elsewhere, he will carry her off on a desperate cross-country misadventure, all in the name of Love. Hilarious, flamboyant, heart-breaking and full of ingenious word play, Lolita is an immaculate, unforgettable masterpiece of obsession, delusion and lust.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1377756377i/7604.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Classics", "Adult", "Fiction", "Novels", "Russian Literature", "Russia", "Literature", "20th Century", "Literary Fiction"], "publisher": "Penguin", "author": ["Craig Raine", "Vladimir Nabokov"], "publishDate": 788947200000, "characters": ["Dolores \u201cLolita\u201d Haze", "Humbert Humbert", "Clare Quilty", "Charlotte Haze"], "places": ["The United States of America"], "ratingHistogram": [32400, 59230, 173752, 272006, 288638], "ratingsCount": 826026, "reviewsCount": 37937, "numPages": 368, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "National Book Award Finalist", "awardedAt": -347126400000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Premios Fervenzas Literarias", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": "Traducci\u00f3n ", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1953.A_Tale_of_Two_Cities", "title": "A Tale of Two Cities", "titleComplete": "A Tale of Two Cities", "description": "A Tale of Two Cities is Charles Dickens\u2019s great historical novel, set against the violent upheaval of the French Revolution. The most famous and perhaps the most popular of his works, it compresses an event of immense complexity to the scale of a family history, with a cast of characters that includes a bloodthirsty ogress and an antihero as believably flawed as any in modern fiction. Though the least typical of the author\u2019s novels, A Tale of Two Cities still underscores many of his enduring themes\u2014imprisonment, injustice, social anarchy, resurrection, and the renunciation that fosters renewal.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1344922523i/1953.jpg", "genres": ["Historical Fiction", "Classics", "British Literature", "Historical", "Fiction", "Novels", "Classic Literature", "Literature", "School", "19th Century"], "asin": "0141439602", "isbn": "0141439602", "isbn13": "9780141439600", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "author": ["Richard Maxwell", "Charles Dickens"], "publishDate": 1041408000000, "characters": ["Sydney Carton", "Dr. Alexandre Manette", "Lucie Manette", "Charles Darnay", "Madame Therese Defarge"], "places": ["London, England", "France", "England", "Paris"], "ratingHistogram": [36222, 70242, 199938, 298224, 325372], "ratingsCount": 929998, "reviewsCount": 22657, "numPages": 489, "language": "English"}
